00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.720
okay so myelodysplastic syndrome what are the challenges i would address we don't cure all

00:00:08.720 --> 00:00:14.440
patients we don't use autologous transplant maybe only chance for cure of this patient

00:00:14.440 --> 00:00:21.120
is allogeneic transplant so where did we get in recent years um i think one of the problem is how

00:00:21.120 --> 00:00:27.180
many patients you have that's how many different mds's you have there is also clonal evolution so

00:00:27.180 --> 00:00:32.120
making the treatment of this disease quite challenging and very few of these mutations

00:00:32.120 --> 00:00:37.520
are targetable then on the other hand i think another challenge is truly this is systemic

00:00:37.520 --> 00:00:46.980
disease and i really like this idea of inflamma aging and autoimmunity and mds so we are not

00:00:46.980 --> 00:00:53.600
treating just bone marrow we are treating the whole body in itself and not surprisingly given

00:00:53.600 --> 00:00:56.260
that complexity is that mds

00:00:56.260 --> 00:00:56.900
including

00:00:57.180 --> 00:01:01.860
increasing with age, but also that the results and outcomes are very similar to those that we

00:01:01.860 --> 00:01:09.700
see with advanced lung cancer in terms of survival outcomes. So moving forward, the goal of treatment

00:01:09.700 --> 00:01:16.580
should be to prevent myeloid-related morbidity and mortality. And this is a slide show MDS natural

00:01:16.580 --> 00:01:22.900
history study. If we just use definition of death and progression, then obviously high-risk MDS

00:01:22.900 --> 00:01:28.260
patients do worse and there is acute rise. But if the outcomes are a little bit changed to include

00:01:28.260 --> 00:01:33.940
worsening disease and cytopenia and need for treatment, we can see that these early diseases

00:01:33.940 --> 00:01:43.240
like CCUS, ICUS also progress over time. And with that excitement is, can we intervene early? I'm

00:01:43.240 --> 00:01:47.840
not going to go over this study. There are different agents currently in the clinical

00:01:47.840 --> 00:01:52.700
trials, whether targeted therapies, metabolic agents, and so on.

00:01:52.900 --> 00:01:58.840
